<TITLE> 'Criminal' killed in Ctg 'shootout' </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Chittagong, May 24 (bdnews24.com)  An alleged criminal was killed in an apparent shootout with RAB and police in the port city early on Monday. The incident occurred near Ananya residential area adjacent to Mohra under Chandgaon upazila at around 3am. A spokesperson from the Rapid Action Battalion (RAB) said that Ali Akkas, 45, was a land grabber and criminal of Jungle Salimpur of the Sitakunda and Islampur area. Akkas and his group had allegedly occupied government khas land in the area and constructed buildings and lived there. There are nine cases and six general diaries lodged against him at different police stations for murder, rape and extortion. Lt Col Sajjad Hossain, chief of RAB-7, told bdnews24.com that two separate groups of RAB and police were on their rounds in the Ananya residential area when around 3am some criminals fired shots at them. Police and RAB fired back in self-defence, exchanging 30 to 35 rounds, said the RAB chief. Akkas died in Chittagong Medical College Hospital after he was taken there from the scene with bullet wounds. RAB has recovered one light machine gun and two bullet casings from the spot. A case has been filed with the Chandgaon Police Station. bdn
